## 🗄️ 2. MongoDB Database Schema (Complete)

### 2.1 `users` Collection

```javascript
// models/user.model.js (Enhanced Schema)
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  
  // Basic Profile
  name: String,                    // "Rahul Sharma"
  phone: String,                   // "9876543210" (10-digit, without 91)
  company_name: String,            // "TechStartup Pvt Ltd"
  bio: String,                     // Free-text bio for vector search
  bio_vector: [Number],            // Gemini embedding (3072 dimensions)
  
  // Categories: "Startup" | "Investor" | "Others"
  category: [String],              // ["Startup", "Investor"]
  
  // Links
  link1: String,                   // LinkedIn / website
  link2: String,                   // Portfolio / other link
  
  // Consent
  consent: Boolean,                // true = visible in recommendations
  
  // Metadata
  searchCount: Number,             // Kitni baar recommend hua (default: 0)
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}

// Indexes:
// { phone: 1 }            — unique, fast lookup
// { category: 1 }         — category filter
// { consent: 1 }          — only consented users recommend hone chahiye
// Vector Index: bio_vector — Atlas Vector Search index
```

---

### 2.2 `seen_recommendations` Collection ⚡ **[NEW — CORE LOGIC]**

> **Ye collection sabse important hai.** Isme track hoga ki kaunse user ne kaunse profile dekhe.

```javascript
// models/seenRecommendation.model.js (NEW FILE BANANA HAI)
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  
  viewerPhone: String,             // Jis user ne dekha — "9876543210"
  seenProfileId: ObjectId,         // Jo profile dekhi — users._id
  seenProfilePhone: String,        // Quick lookup ke liye
  category: String,                // "Startup" | "Investor" | "Others"
  
  seenAt: Date,                    // Kab dekha (timestamps se)
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}

// Indexes:
// Compound: { viewerPhone: 1, seenProfileId: 1 } — UNIQUE (duplicate prevent)
// { viewerPhone: 1, category: 1 }                — category-wise filter
// { viewerPhone: 1, seenAt: 1 }                  — daily limit check ke liye
// TTL Index optional: { seenAt: 1 } with expireAfterSeconds (agar reset chahiye)
```

---

### 2.3 `connection_requests` Collection

> Yeh already exist karta hai tumhare codebase mein. Thoda enhance karenge.

```javascript
// models/connectionRequest.model.js (Existing — Enhanced)
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  
  senderPhone: String,             // User A — "9876543210"
  receiverPhone: String,           // User B — "9123456789"
  
  // Status lifecycle: pending → accepted | rejected
  status: {
    type: String,
    enum: ["pending", "accepted", "rejected"],
    default: "pending"
  },
  
  // 11za Template Tracking
  templateMessageId: String,       // 11za ka messageId (notification track karne ke liye)
  
  // Timestamps
  acceptedAt: Date,                // Jab accept hua
  rejectedAt: Date,                // Jab reject hua
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}

// Indexes:
// { senderPhone: 1, receiverPhone: 1 } — UNIQUE (duplicate request prevent)
// { senderPhone: 1, status: 1 }        — chatbotSearch mein exclusion ke liye
// { receiverPhone: 1, status: 1 }      — incoming requests dekhe ke liye
```

---

### 2.4 `daily_limits` Collection ⚡ **[NEW]**

> Ek user ek din mein maximum 5 recommendations dekh sakta hai — isko track karne ke liye.

```javascript
// models/dailyLimit.model.js (NEW FILE BANANA HAI)
{
  _id: ObjectId,
  
  phone: String,                   // User ka phone — "9876543210"
  date: String,                    // "2024-03-10" (YYYY-MM-DD format)
  count: Number,                   // Aaj kitne dekhe (default: 0)
  
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}

// Indexes:
// Compound UNIQUE: { phone: 1, date: 1 } — ek user ka ek din mein ek hi record
// TTL Index: { createdAt: 1 } expireAfterSeconds: 604800 (7 days auto-cleanup)
```

