## 🔧 3. Recommendation Filtering Logic — Step by Step

```
getNextRecommendation(userPhone, category)
│
├── Step 1: DAILY LIMIT CHECK
│   └── daily_limits.findOne({ phone, date: today })
│       ├── count >= 5? → Return "Daily limit reached" message
│       └── count < 5? → Continue
│
├── Step 2: GET SEEN IDs
│   └── seen_recommendations.find({ viewerPhone: userPhone })
│       └── .select('seenProfileId') → seenIds[] array
│
├── Step 3: GET SENT REQUEST IDs  
│   └── connection_requests.find({ senderPhone: userPhone, status: {$in: ['pending','accepted']} })
│       └── Map receiverPhone → User._id → sentUserIds[] array
│
├── Step 4: MERGE ALL EXCLUSIONS
│   └── allExcludedIds = [...seenIds, ...sentUserIds, userOwnId]
│
├── Step 5: VECTOR SEARCH QUERY
│   └── $vectorSearch → bio_vector
│       ├── Filter: _id: { $nin: allExcludedIds }
│       ├── Filter: category: { $in: [requestedCategory] }
│       ├── Filter: consent: true
│       └── Limit: 1 result
│
├── Step 6: NO RESULTS CHECK
│   └── results.length === 0?
│       ├── Check: Kya saari recommendations dekh li hain?
│       │   └── users.countDocuments({ category, consent:true }) === seenIds.length?
│       │       └── YES → Return "Thank You / No More Recommendations" message
│       │                  (DO NOT reset loop)
│       └── Partial miss → Return same "No more available" message
│
└── Step 7: SAVE SEEN + INCREMENT COUNTER
    ├── seen_recommendations.insertOne({ viewerPhone, seenProfileId, category })
    ├── daily_limits.findOneAndUpdate({ phone, date }, { $inc: { count: 1 } }, { upsert: true })
    └── users.updateOne({ _id: result._id }, { $inc: { searchCount: 1 } })
```

